1. *Nedeljama* ne izlazim iz kuće. (For weeks, I haven't been leaving the house.)
2. Neću moći da se vidim s tobom *nedeljama*. (I won't be able to see you for weeks.)
3. Ova knjiga *nedeljama* mi je bila na čitanju. (I've been reading this book for weeks.)
4. U gradu su *nedeljama* trajale proteste. (Protests have been going on in the city for weeks.)
5. *Nedeljama* je padala kiša, ali sada je konačno prestala. (It rained for weeks, but it has finally stopped now.)
6. Poslednje *nedelje* su bile jako stresne za mene. (The past few weeks have been very stressful for me.)
7. Svakog ponedeljka *nedeljama* odlazim na jogu. (I've been going to yoga every Monday for weeks.)
8. *Nedeljama* sam se pripremao za ovaj ispit. (I've been preparing for this exam for weeks.)

Note: In Serbian, "nedeljama" is the plural form of "nedelja" which means "week" in English. It can be used to indicate a duration of time or a repeated action over a period of weeks.